    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Esopus-on-Hudson</name>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">New York</name>
                    <date when="1877-03-17">March 17</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dearest friend</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>After a couple of weeks in New York, Mr Burroughs has brought me up here, where I am to stay for a few days&#8212;Every thing goes well&#8212;I am very comfortably situated, &amp; it is not only a great change from <choice><abbr>N Y</abbr><expan>New York</expan></choice>&#8212;but a great relief&#8212;I mean the excitement of so much company&#8212;every thing is quiet &amp; secluded here&#8212;all winter too, the snow white &amp; deep in every direction&#8212;as I look from my window, river &amp; mountains &amp; trees &amp; rocks&#8212;far &amp; vast&#8212;</p>
               
            <p>I only write a hurried line to let you know my whereabouts&#8212;Shall (probably) be returning to Camden latter part of next week&#8212;Love to all&#8212;</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
